[The number of laboratory-confirmed human cases in Thailand has increased
to 5, all of whom are now deceased. The total number of
laboratory-confirmed human cases of avian influenza A (H5N1) virus
infection in Viet Nam has increased to 15, including 11 deaths. This brings
the total number of human cases of avian influenza A (H5N1) virus infection
in East Asia to 20, and the total number of deaths to 16. Thailand and Viet
Nam remain the only 2 countries in the region to have recorded human cases
of avian influenza A (H5N1) virus infection. - Mod.CP]
